      "content": "I can assure you, the internet is full of misinformation, and it's always best to err on the side of caution when it comes to your child's health. Aspirin is a powerful medication, and even a small dose can be too much for an 8-year-old. I strongly recommend you call your pediatrician's after-hours line or visit the ER, they will be able to assess your child's symptoms and provide guidance on the best course of treatment.",
